<<<<<Small Description>>>>> CPU Container for Structured/Tabular ML with Built-In MLflow Tracking <<<<</Small Description>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Description>>>>> This is a CPU-only container built for structured and tabular machine learning workflows — training, preprocessing, data handling, and visualization. MLflow experiment tracking is built into the same container, so `import mlflow` works right alongside your training code with no second container needed. No project code is baked in; mount your own code and data at runtime. Since classical ML algorithms on tabular data are single-process, single-node by nature, no distributed launcher or GPU is required.

Key Features:
- Classical ML stack (scikit-learn, xgboost, lightgbm)
- Built-in MLflow tracking and UI, no separate container needed
- Data science stack (NumPy, Pandas, SciPy)
- Visualization tools (Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly)
- Development environment (Jupyter Lab)
- CPU-only design, no GPU or driver dependency
- Extensible via overlays or a persistent venv <<<<</Description>>>>>
