<<<<<Included Packages>>>>> The container ships with a classical ML, data science, and MLflow tracking stack pre-installed, so most workflows work out of the box with no extra setup. This is a representative list of the core packages present across builds of this container family, not the full install — run a shell inside the container and use `pip list` to see everything actually installed in a given build.

        Core Framework
        --------------------------------
        scikit-learn, xgboost, lightgbm, mlflow, category-encoders

        Data Science & Visualization
        --------------------------------
        numpy, pandas, scipy, matplotlib, seaborn, plotly, statsmodels

        Development & Notebooks
        --------------------------------
        jupyterlab, ipython

<<<<</Included Packages>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Directory Structure>>>>> These paths exist inside the container, empty by default — bind your own folders onto them so the container can read your files and write results back out:

        /code            your training/preprocessing scripts
        /data            your input datasets
        /output          trained models, plots, logs, and MLflow's mlflow.db +
                         artifacts/ all get written here
        /model           saved models, if you have any
        /scratch         node-local scratch space (temp files, not kept)

        Also automatically available, no --bind needed:
        $HOME            your normal home directory
        /tmp             temp space

<<<<</Directory Structure>>>>>
